title: Rescuing Abandoned Dogs Is His Rehab
excerpt: Mike Favor spent 13 years addicted to cocaine. Running a shelter for abandoned and abused dogs has helped him and others stay sober. But it hasn’t been easy.

title: How America Saved Millions of Dogs—By Moving Them
excerpt: How adoptable animals became a cultural phenomenon in their own right, and a key part of a transformation of companion-animal welfare.
